Accessibility First

In modern applications, accessibility is non-negotiable. Building custom dropdown overlays that screen readers can interpret is notoriously difficult. ng-tel-input-autocomplete solves this out of the box:

•
WAI-ARIA Compliance: Implements the combobox role on the input, listbox on the dropdown overlay, and option on each item.

•
Keyboard Navigation: Arrows select items, Enter confirms, and Escape closes the dropdown.

•
Screen Reader Feedback: Dynamic announcements are made when a search is loading, empty, or returns results, ensuring a seamless experience for visually impaired users.

Wrapping Up

Whether you are building a simple contact form or a complex CRM panel, ng-tel-input-autocomplete provides the robustness, accessibility, and performance needed for modern web development.

